  "text": "Fault Tolerance is a crucial property for Neural Networks to ensure reliable computation for long duration and graceful degradation over time. Typically, well generalised models have the parameters with low variance ensuring equal computational weightage to all nodes in the network. Hence, loss of some of the nodes can be compensated by other nodes without a significant loss in performance [CITATION_1] ) [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Practically, this is achieved by adding noise during training to the inputs, gradients or the weights.",
